# Vobiz development rules

Read `skills/vobiz-api/SKILL.md` before handling a Vobiz integration. Load the
specialized `skills/vobiz-*/SKILL.md` file that matches the requested domain.

- Verify uncertain or changing behavior with `https://vobiz.ai/docs/introduction`,
  `https://vobiz.ai/openapi.json`, or `https://vobiz.ai/docs/mcp`.
- Use `https://api.vobiz.ai/api/v1` as the REST base URL.
- Preserve endpoint path casing exactly.
- Use `X-Auth-ID` and `X-Auth-Token` for server-side REST authentication unless
  the current endpoint documentation explicitly supports another method.
- Keep credentials in environment variables or a secret manager. Never print
  or commit them.
- Encode `+` as `%2B` in E.164 URL path parameters.
- Require explicit confirmation before billable, destructive, money-moving, or
  externally visible actions.
- Do not invent endpoints, fields, prices, limits, or product behavior.

